{
  "stem": "10572.2",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And you also asked before, what made us not see the upcoming or the oncoming danger?",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Thus, thought of my sister Edith, got married to Egon Rehfeld in 1937.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Egon's father was the president of our congregation.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And as their wedding present in June, 1937, they got a trip to America.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they came to Atlantic City and stayed in Atlantic City on their honeymoon.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Now, anybody in his right mind in 1937, even I, would have at least put out my feelers and say, you know, what is a America all about?",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Isn't this some day a place that I better find out and make my contacts now, instead of being on a honeymoon and lying on the beach in Atlantic City?",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They came back-- Edith with her jewels-- came back to Hildesheim.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And Edith at that time-- she was very young, she was 19 years old-- told her father-in-law, her new father-in law, that maybe they had  made a mistake.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Maybe they should have looked around while they were in America.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And Alex Rehfeld, the patriarch of the family, looked at my sister and said, you ungrateful child.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I have taken care of you, your children, and children's children.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And you don't ever have to worry of going to America.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "That was in 1937.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "A year later, when he was on his way to Buchenwald and after he came out of Buchenwald, he  had changed his tune a little bit and wasn't quite sure if the God that he had served for so many years as the head of the congregation was really alive and if he could really trust him.",
      "word_count": 57
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And he thought of a possibility of going, packing up the next day and going to Shanghai.",
      "word_count": 17
    }
  ],
